<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2469> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2469" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Fulvius M. f. succeeded P. Manlius (Vulso ?). Liv. 40.42.7. Tum praetextatus (Liv.)" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2456> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2456" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Province: Farther Spain. Died shortly after his return (Liv. 40.41.10, and 42.7)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2422> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2422" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His imperium was prorogued in Farther Spain (Liv. 40.18.6), where he fought with the Lusitani (40.34.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2421> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2421" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See note 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2393> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2393" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Brought new troops and restored the discipline of the army (Liv. 40.1.4, and 16.7-10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2392> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2392" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cato expelled from the Senate a certain Manilius who was thought to have good prospects for the consulship (Plut. Cat. Mai. 17.7). We know no ex-Praetor of the name who would be elegible, but we find P. Manlius becoming Praetor for the second time soon afterwards. He may possibly be identified with Manilius. See 196, note 9." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2390> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2390" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elections: Liv. 39.51.5 Provinces and armies 40.1.1-2 and 4 and 7." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2071> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2071" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "An aide to the Consul Cato (Liv. 33.43.5 and 8). Carried on war actively in Turdetania (Liv. 34.17-19; cf. 40.16.7, Ulterior, and 39.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2068> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2068" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 33.42.7 Provinces and armies 33.43.5-8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2066> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2066" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected this year for the first time (Liv. 33.42.1). On Porcius, see D.- G., no. 7; Lübker, no. 12.{339}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2065> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2065" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Against the statement of Klose (92) and the suggestion of Münzer (RE) that he was a Vulso and a patrician is the fact that his successor was a plebeian (Liv. 40.42.7). See Mommsen, RF 1.90f. On the founding of the priesthood see Cic. De Or. 3.73." .
